-- Richfield to Place Up to 150 Million Shares at HK$1.20 Each; Borrows Loan
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-10-21T15:06:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/richfield-to-place-up-to-150-million-shares-at-hk-1-20-each-borrows-loan.html
Richfield Group Holdings Ltd . will
place 150 million shares at HK$1.20 each, raising a net HK$174
million for “general working capital,” the company said in a
Hong Kong stock exchange filing today.  The company said in a separate Hong Kong filing that it has
borrowed HK$490 million for as long as five years to finance a
real estate project.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  